这次航行的初步研究发现，太平洋垃圾带的绝大多数漂浮垃圾都是小东西<ref name=UCSDNews28Sep09/>，很小一部分垃圾无处不在，自水面到深海都有分布<ref name=SDDN27Aug09>{{Cite news
 |url         = http://www.sdnn.com/sandiego/2009-08-27/news/‘shocking’-amount-of-plastic-pollutes-oceans
 |title       = ‘Shocking’ amount of plastic pollutes oceans
 |publisher   = [[San_Diego_News_Network|San Diego News Network]]
 |date        = 2009-08-27
 |accessdate  = 2009-09-30
 |deadurl     = yes
 |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20090831091702/http://www.sdnn.com/sandiego/2009-08-27/news/%E2%80%98shocking%E2%80%99-amount-of-plastic-pollutes-oceans
 |archivedate = 2009-08-31
}}</ref>。研究还发现，“小的彩色塑料碎片多的难以想象”，越靠近垃圾带中心，垃圾密度越大<ref name=Mercury1Sep09/>。发现表明，与海洋生物大小相仿的的垃圾可能会给清理工作带来很大困难<ref name=ReutersUK28Aug09/>。

大型的垃圾漂浮物主要是塑料瓶，还包括鞋底、塑料桶、泡沫塑料片、旧玩具、渔船浮标，大量垃圾漂浮物与渔网缠在一起<ref name=Mercury1Sep09/><ref name=NSFRelease27Aug09/>。这些有各种海洋生物生活在大型垃圾漂浮物内部和周围<ref name=NSFRelease27Aug09>{{cite press release
 |url         = http://www.nsf.gov/news/news_summ.jsp?cntn_id=115481&org=NSF&from=news
 |title       = Scientists Find "Great Pacific Ocean Garbage Patch"
